div.p:
Further, our program provides the following four safeguards: 

First, and most important, SCAP, by
                            virtue of authority already granted to him in FEC policy, may retain any industrial plant needed for the
                            purposes of the occupation, that is, any facilities needed for achieving
                            Japanese economic self-support;

Second, claimant countries are required to pay the costs of
                            transportation;

Third, claimant countries must complete removals within two years;



Fourth, claimant countries must provide evidence that removed facilities
                            are capable of practical use in their countries.
